description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ashton, Leigh &amp; Wigan Specialist Weight Management Service (SWMS) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Psychologist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;WTE: 0.6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pay band: Band 8a / Band 7 preceptorship&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contract: Temporary 9 – 12 months&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role would be suitable for a newly qualified Psychologist looking for their first qualified role as well as an established Psychologist looking to gain more experience in weight management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a Clinical Psychologist with relevant experience to join our well established Specialist Weight Management service, based in various community settings across the Wigan Borough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post offers a rare opportunity to join a dynamic team to contribute to on going service developments. The post affords excellent opportunities for professional development and consolidation of expertise, within the sphere of weight management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic individual, with excellent interpersonal and communication skills and an excellent professional attitude. Relevant clinical experience that can offer transferable competencies is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous clinical experience in the area of weight management psychology is preferable (in the absence of this, previous clinical experience in the areas of diabetes or eating disorders will be viewed favourably). Experience of both direct and indirect models of working (e.g. providing consultation/ training/ supervision) is desirable; together with clinical experience of using third wave cognitive behavioural therapies in clinical work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to work flexible hours, including evenings, in line with supporting the clinical delivery model in place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome applications from suitably qualified, enthusiastic and highly motivated individuals with a positive professional attitude, appropriate depth of clinical experience and who are interested in actively supporting the on going development of a thriving MDT service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be professionally line managed by the well-established Clinical Health Psychology Department based at Aintree Hospital and Operationally Line managed by the Service Operational Lead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Adrienne Smith (Operational Lead) on 01942 483370 or Victoria Molyneaux (Clinical Psychologist) on: 0151 529 3251. Alternatively you can email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;adrienne.smith@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;victoria.molyneaux@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications will be closed when enough suitable applications have been received&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAdrienne SmithJob titleSWMS Operational LeadEmail addressadrienne.smith@liverpoolft.nhs.ukTelephone number01942 483370&lt;/p&gt;
